    <body>
        <title>EPPO simple list</title>
        
        <p> An ordered or unordered list may follow an initial <feature>paragraph</feature>,
            <feature> fragment </feature>, or <feature> fragment reference </feature> in the
            <feature> body content </feature> of a topic.</p>

        <fig href="../../../graphics/list-context.png">
                <title>EPPO-simple list context</title>
                <caption>
                    <p></p>
                </caption>
            </fig>
            
        <p> </p>

        <section>
            <title>Structure</title>

            <p> An ordered (<xml-element-name>ol</xml-element-name>) list has the structure shown in
                the following <feature> structure diagram </feature>:</p>

            <fig href="../../../graphics/ol.png">
                <title>Ordered list structure diagram</title>
                <caption><p></p></caption>
            </fig>

            <p> An unordered list (<xml-element-name>ul</xml-element-name>) list has the same
                structure: </p>

            <fig href="../../../graphics/ul.png">
                <title>Unordered list structure diagram</title>
                <caption><p></p></caption>
            </fig>

        </section>

        <section>
            <title>Example</title>
            <p> The following XML markup produces the lists that follows.</p>
            <codeblock>
<![CDATA[
        <p> Procedure for making french-press coffee:</p>
        <ol>
            <li> <p> Grind coffee beans. </p> </li>
            <li> <p> Place ground coffee beans in french press. </p> </li>
            <li> <p> Fill french press with hot water just off a boil. </p> </li>
            <li> <p> Let steep for four minutes. </p> </li>
            <li> <p> Pour yourself a fresh cup of <italic>hot</italic> coffee. </p> </li>
        </ol>

        <p> Fruit for the trip: </p>
        <ul>
            <li> <p> Apples </p> </li>
            <li> <p> Oranges </p> </li>
            <li> <p> Bananas </p> </li>
        </ul>
]]>
            </codeblock>
            
            <p> Procedure for making french-press coffee:</p>
            <ol>
                <li> <p> Grind coffee beans. </p> </li>
                <li> <p> Place ground coffee beans in french press. </p> </li>
                <li> <p> Fill french press with hot water just off a boil. </p> </li>
                <li> <p> Let steep for four minutes. </p> </li>
                <li> <p> Pour yourself a fresh cup of <italic>hot</italic> coffee. </p> </li>
            </ol>

            <p> Fruit for the trip: </p>
            <ul>
                <li> <p> Apples </p> </li>
                <li> <p> Oranges </p> </li>
                <li> <p> Bananas </p> </li>
            </ul>
            
        </section>
        
